collection.title: Matson (G. Eric and Edith) Photograph Collection
collection.brief: Images made by the American Colony Photo Department and its successor, the Matson Photo Service, illustrating Middle East culture, history, and political events including people and locations in Palestine (present day Israel, the West Bank and Gaza Strip), Jordan, Lebanon, Syria, Iraq, Egypt, and Turkey.
collection.banner_title: Camel transport, Olivet. American Colony Photo Dept., 1918.
collection.extent: Over 23,000 negatives, transperencies and photographic prints.
